<p class="MsoNormal">Jake Desyllas from <em style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal;">The Voluntary Life</em> podcast joins me to talk about financial freedom. <span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>What is financial freedom?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>What are the different paths to get there?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>How does investing fit in?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>What about real estate?</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">We cover a great deal of ground in the conversation, dipping into related topics and not so related topics.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>What are the economics of voluntarism?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>Why does communism fail?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>How does the family relate to government?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>How does the family relate to a job you might take?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>All of that, and much, much more!</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Find more from Jake here:<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span><a href="http://www.thevoluntarylife.com/">http://www.thevoluntarylife.com/</a></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">His new book:<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span><a href="http://www.thevoluntarylife.com/p/books.html">http://www.thevoluntarylife.com/p/books.html</a></p>
