<tr><td><div class="postDate">Mon, 2 July 2012</div>
<div class="postTitle"><a href='http://traffic.libsyn.com/choiceconversations/Episode_117_-_A_Bit_About_BitCoin.mp3'><img src='http://assets.libsyn.com/podcastIcon.gif' border='0' align='left'></a>
<a class="postTitle" href='http://choiceconversations.libsyn.com/episode-117-a-bit-about-bit-coin'>Episode 117 - A Bit About BitCoin</a>
</div> <!-- end postTitle -->
<div class="postBody">
	<p>A while has passed since our last podcast but after a long break I'm back with a podcast about Bit Coin.</p>
<p>Bit Coin is a digital currency that is not affiliated with any person, country, or nation. It is an independently operating currency that is very much still in it's infancy after almost four years of being circulated. But in this interview Brian Nugent explains that Bit Coin is not just some passing fancy, it is actually an emergent technology that has the momentum to upend the current monetary system... or to out it more bluntly, the current monetary regime.&nbsp;</p>
<p>This interview is an eye-opening look into what could very well be the future of money. Please don't miss this informative podcast.</p>
<p><a href="https://blockchain.info/wallet/">Open a BitCoin Account</a></p>
<p>Donate to my BitCoin Wallet -&nbsp;<a class="pop" data-content="These are your personal bitcoin addresses. Share these with people and they can send you bitcoins." href="https://blockchain.info/address/14ZF5Vpz9SSwdXkJAsDtHcRsUYSJAF2R16" target="new" data-original-title="Your Addresses" style="color: #0088cc; text-decoration: none; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px; text-align: left; background-color: #f9f9f9;">14ZF5Vpz9SSwdXkJAsDtHcRsUYSJAF2R16</a></p>
<p><a href="https://blockchain.info/charts">Interesting Data about BitCoin</a></p>
<p></p>
