<tr><td><div class="postDate">Tue, 6 December 2011</div>
<div class="postTitle"><a href='http://traffic.libsyn.com/choiceconversations/Episode_105_-_The_Tea_Party_is_Based_on_a_False_Premise.mp3'><img src='http://assets.libsyn.com/podcastIcon.gif' border='0' align='left'></a>
<a class="postTitle" href='http://choiceconversations.libsyn.com/episode-105-the-tea-party-is-based-on-a-false-premise'>Episode 105 - The Tea Party is Based on a False Premise</a>
</div> <!-- end postTitle -->
<div class="postBody">
	<p>Just me and my Iphone App, recording a vignette as I sit in my office.</p>
<p>The argument I am making, "The Tea Party is Based on False Premise", is one that I make often to people who associate themselves with the Tea Party. Needless to say, I don't get invited back to Tea Party parties.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The song I chose for close out the show is 'The Debtor' by Miles Benjamin Anthony. His entire album is great but this song in particular stands out above the rest.</p>
</div> <!-- end postBody -->
