<tr><td><div class="postDate">Fri, 3 December 2010</div>
<div class="postTitle"><a href='http://traffic.libsyn.com/choiceconversations/Episode_73_-_Plateau_Oil_vs_Peak_Oil.mp3'><img src='http://assets.libsyn.com/podcastIcon.gif' border='0' align='left'></a>
<a class="postTitle" href='http://choiceconversations.libsyn.com/plateau-oil-vs-peak-oil-with-steve-crower'>Plateau Oil vs. Peak Oil with Steve Crower</a>
</div> <!-- end postTitle -->
<div class="postBody">
	<p>Steve Crower returns to give his latest insight on Peak Oil, or rather the introduction of the term 'Plateau Oil'. The Plateau Oil term refers to the introduction of both new technologies that increase the existing oil fields (marginally improving the yield) and new technologies that bring shale oil to the market. The effect will be a plateau-ing of oil production or, to put it differently, oil supply. The demand part of this equation remains a question mark but we spend most of our time in this interview discussing the supply side.</p>
<p>Thanks for the generous donation from Peak Oil Medicine, here is the&nbsp;<a href="PostPeakMedicine.com">website</a>.&nbsp;<a href="http://www.PostPeakMedicine.com">www.PostPeakMedicine.com</a></p>
</div> <!-- end postBody -->
<div class="postDetails">
Direct download: <a href='http://traffic.libsyn.com/choiceconversations/Episode_73_-_Plateau_Oil_vs_Peak_Oil.mp3'>Episode_73_-_Plateau_Oil_vs_Peak_Oil.mp3</a><br>
