<div class="postTitle"><a href='http://traffic.libsyn.com/choiceconversations/Episode_64_-_Ferfal_on_Argentinas_Collapse.mp3'><img src='http://assets.libsyn.com/podcastIcon.gif' border='0' align='left'></a>
<a class="postTitle" href='http://choiceconversations.libsyn.com/ferfal-on-the-argentina-s-2002-collapse'>Ferfal on the Argentina's 2002 Collapse</a>
</div> <!-- end postTitle -->
<div class="postBody">
	<p><img id="rg_hi" class="rg_hi" style="width: 240px; float: left; height: 181px;" src="http://t2.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQ6BHveFoNLbciwnY0vTia6MgvOO7VTWJycIHDj8xctwmhUiQ8&amp;t=1&amp;usg=__WMnwp9splhA6C5hfjY-frxMdGCw=" alt="" width="240" height="181" /></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Rioting, protesting in the streets, chaos, political and social unrest.</p>
<p>This describes the collapse of the Argentinian economy and the hyperinflation of its currency. In 2002 the people of Argentina experienced such a scenario and I talk with Fernando Aguire who blogs from Buenos Aires about what is was like to experience it firsthand and what he thinks are similiarities and differences in&nbsp;our situation in the US.</p>
<p><a href="http://ferfal.blogspot.com/">Surviving in Argentina Website</a></p>
<p>Ferfal's book <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Modern-Survival-Manual-Surviving-Economic/dp/9870563457/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1285992109&amp;sr=8-1">Modern Survival Manual</a>: Surviving the Economic Collapse which has 4.5 Stars on Amazon.com</p>
