<tr><td><div class="postDate">Wed, 10 February 2010</div>
<div class="postTitle"><a href='http://traffic.libsyn.com/choiceconversations/The_Effect_of_Peak_Oil_on_Healthcare.mp3'><img src='http://assets.libsyn.com/podcastIcon.gif' border='0' align='left'></a>
<a class="postTitle" href='http://choiceconversations.libsyn.com/peak-oil-and-it-s-effect-on-the-healthcare-industry'>Peak Oil And It's Effect On The Healthcare Industry</a>
</div> <!-- end postTitle -->
<div class="postBody">
	<img src ="http://assets.libsyn.com/content/2561314" class="postImage" >
	<p>What compels people of all walks of life to break from the herd and begin the process of self-education? In this episode we talk with Dr. Peter Gray who explains what were the decisions he made that broke him from the&nbsp;pack and why he thinks his industry, healthcare, is overlooking a very serious threat... Peak Oil.</p>
<p>As always we explore a multitude of topics including medicinal marijuana and the increased use of tranquilizers by Americans. And since we have a Canadian doctor why not ask him what he thinks of the American healthcare debate?</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
